<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="1379" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1379">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/222.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Carothers</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-09">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 9, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Carranza undoubtedly gave statement to press to effect that property
                                of Spaniards will not be confiscated. I fear he will take no action
                                with Villa considering his former statement to me that he would not
                                interfere with the orders given by Villa. Cotton belonging to
                                Spaniards and others, among it six cars belonging to Purcell and
                                Co., is beginning to arrive in Juarez. I believe Carranza will go to
                                Chihuahua to meet Villa who will go there from Torreon about Sunday,
                                the 12th. I believe he will take no action whatever until after the
                                meeting.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">G C. Carothers</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>